    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-02T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="658"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d658">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> Telegram File: frc Acc. No. 53A278: Ankara
                        <gloss target="#t_Ecato1">Ecato</gloss>: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Administrator for Economic Cooperation</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_FWC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foster</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">
                            <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> Mission in Turkey</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d658fn1">Authorized by <persName corresp="#p_HDK1"
                            >Hopkinson</persName>, <gloss target="#t_EPDECA1">EPD/ECA</gloss>;
                        drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BWM1">Blaisdell</persName>, <gloss
                            target="#t_EPDECA1">EPD/ECA</gloss>; and cleared with <persName
                            corresp="#p_GCS1">Clarence S. Gulick</persName>, <gloss
                            target="#t_EPDECA1">EPD/ECA</gloss>; <persName corresp="#p_DCN1">de
                            Paul</persName>, <gloss target="#t_EPDECA1">EPD/ECA</gloss>; and
                            <persName corresp="#p_BRW1">Bissell</persName>, <gloss target="#t_ECA1"
                            >ECA</gloss>. It was repeated to Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-02T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 2, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Ecato1">Ecato</gloss> 292. 1. <persName corresp="#p_BRW1"
                        >Bissell</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_EFC2">Erkin</persName> conference
                    held 30 April. <persName corresp="#p_EFC2">Erkin</persName> disappointed at
                    level of aid but <persName corresp="#p_BRW1">Bissell</persName> emphasized
                    increase above expected $52.2 million and urged that <persName corresp="#p_EFC2"
                        >Erkin</persName> impress on his Gov importance of prompt action so that
                    entire $70 million might be used prior to 30 June. <persName corresp="#p_BRW1"
                        >Bissell</persName> also emphasized general policy statements set forth in
                    memo. (Ref <gloss target="#t_Ecato1">Ecato</gloss> 263 rptd Paris <gloss
                        target="#t_Torep1">Torep</gloss> 2541)<note n="2" xml:id="d658fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> After conference <persName corresp="#p_EFC2"
                        >Erkin</persName> telephoned to inquire whether special $4 million <gloss
                        target="#t_NCO1">NCO</gloss> allotment included in $70 million. Arithmetic
                    set forth in para 1 of memo was further elaborated for him, indicating inclusion
                    of $4 million.</p>
                <p>2. <persName corresp="#p_EFC2">Erkin</persName> handed to <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRW1">Bissell</persName> short memo urging that U.S. take
                    favorable position on Turk request for additional <gloss target="#t_EPU1"
                        >EPU</gloss> initial position for current year.<note n="2" xml:id="d658fn3"
                        >Not printed.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BRW1">Bissell</persName> replied that he was not in a
                    position to give <persName corresp="#p_EFC2">Erkin</persName> any encouragement
                    on this item and emphasized that $70 million level was established as upper
                    limit of assistance to Turkey from current U.S. <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                        >FY</gloss> funds. However, <persName corresp="#p_BRW1">Bissell</persName>
                    suggested that Turk Gov might be interested in shifting some direct dollar
                    assistance to <gloss target="#t_EPU1">EPU</gloss> assistance, without increasing
                    total level of aid.</p>
                <p>3. <persName corresp="#p_BRW1">Bissell</persName> indicated to <persName
                        corresp="#p_EFC2">Erkin</persName> that <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>
                    aid to Turkey from U.S. <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 52 funds would be
                    projected as of same order of magnitude as current year’s aid but that greater
                    portion of aid through <gloss target="#t_EPU1">EPU</gloss> and smaller portion
                    in form of direct dollars. No figures mentioned by <persName corresp="#p_BRW1"
                        >Bissell</persName> in this connection.</p>
                <p>4. State Department representative present at meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FWC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foster</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
